title: Jepson Ecoregions
name: Jepson Ecoregions
description: The Jepson geographic system is organized heirarchically, starting with broadly defined provinces and ending with districts (third-order subdivisions of provinces). There are 50 geographic units in this system. Each has a unique abbreviation, used in descriptions and keys. Each of the 50 units is described in the front material of TJMII.
